SYNTAX : 
    
    awk -Options 'Pattern_OR_Condition {Action}' Filename 
    Other_commands | awk -Options 'Pattern_OR_Condition {Action}' Filename 


FIELD OR COLUMN : 

    GET Nth AND Mth FIELD : awk '{print $N, $M}' Filename

    GET ALL FIELDS : awk '{print $0}' Filename

    GET LAST FIELD : awk '{print $NF}' Filename


ROW OR RECORD : 

    GET NtH LINE : awk 'NR==N {print $0}' Filename

    GET RANGE OF LINES Nth TO Mth : awk 'NR==N,NR==M {print $0}' Filename

    PRINT LINE NUMBER BEFORE EACH LINE DATA : awk '{print NR, $0}' Filename

    GET LINE NUMBER OF EMPTY LINES : awk 'NF==0 {print NR }' Filename


CSV AND DELIMITER : 

    SINGLE DELIMITER : awk -F "delimiter"'{print $0}' Filename

    MULTIPLE DELIMITER : awk -F[D1D2D3] "delimiter"'{print $0}' Filename


SEARCH : 

    GET ROWS CONTAINING A WORD : awk '/SearchWord/{print $0}' Filename

    GET LINES CONTAINING THESE WORDS : awk '/Word1|Word2|Word3/{print $0}' Filename

    IGNORE CASE SENSITIVE WHILE SEARCH : awk 'BEGIN{IGNORECASE=1} /Word/{print $0}' Filename

    GET LINES WHOSE Nth COLUMN CONTAIN CHARACTOR X : awk '$N ~ /X/ {print $0}' Filename


FILTER : 

    GET LINES WITH Nth FIELD VALUES MORE THAN EQUAL TO NUM : awk '$NF>=NUM {print $0}' Filename


SOME FUNCTIONS :  

    REPLACE WORD1 WITH WORD2 AND PRINT :  awk '{gsub("word1","word2") ;print $0}' Filename

    LENGTH OF ELEMENTS IN Nth FIELD : awk '{print length($N)}' Filename

    LENGTH OF EACH LINE : awk '{print length($0)}' Filename

    INDEX OF FIRST CHARACTOR OF SEARCHWORD : awk '{print index($0,"SearchWord")}'

    CONVERT TO LOWER CASE : awk 'print tolower($0)' Filename

    CONVERT TO UPPER CASE : awk 'print toupper($0)' Filename


AWK SCRIPTING SYNTAX : 

    awk
        'BEGIN{start_actions}
            Pattern_Condition{Action}
        END{stop_actin}'
    Filename


AWK FILE : 

    awk -F "delimiter" -f File.awk Filename

